study_pop.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. All participants must be ≥ 18 years old;

          2. Study subjects had definite diagnosis based on gonioscopy, optical coherence
             tomography (OCT) and medical history records.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Poor compliance in receiving gonioscopy examination;

          2. Unclear anterior segment OCT scans due to blinking or out of focus;

          3. Recent use of miotics within a month;

          4. Secondary angle closure sue to subluxation or dislocation, uveitis, neovascular
             glaucoma;

          5. History of ocular surgery or laser; 6) Patients who previously had an episode of acute
             attack.

criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. All participants must be ≥ 18 years old;

          2. Study subjects had definite diagnosis based on gonioscopy, optical coherence
             tomography (OCT) and medical history records.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Poor compliance in receiving gonioscopy examination;

          2. Unclear anterior segment OCT scans due to blinking or out of focus;

          3. Recent use of miotics within a month;

          4. Secondary angle closure sue to subluxation or dislocation, uveitis, neovascular
             glaucoma;

          5. History of ocular surgery or laser; 6) Patients who previously had an episode of acute
             attack.
